<h4>Fastest Lap</h4>

<p>5 points will be allocated if your driver achieves the fastest lap in the race.</p>

<h4>Race Finish</h4>

<p>5 points will be allocated if your driver finishes the race. As per the formula one regulations, any driver who completes over 90 percent of the race will be classified as a finisher, regardless of whether they were running as the winner took the chequered flag</p>

<h4>Teammates</h4>

<p>5 points will be allocated if your driver finishes ahead of their teammate.</p>
<hr />
<h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag">&nbsp;</span>Constructor Points</h3>

<p>5 points will be awarded if a <u>single</u> car in your chosen constructor finishes the race. 20 points will be awarded if <u>both</u> cars finish the race. An additional 5 points will be awarded per car finishing in the top 10.</p>
<hr />
<h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag">&nbsp;</span>Engine Points</h3>

<p>Mercedes, Ferrari and Renault (only): 15 points are awarded per car(*) finishing the race in the top 5 with your chosen engine.</p>
<p>Honda (only): 20 points are awarded per car(*) finishing the race in the top 10 with your chosen engine.</p>
<p>*Engine points are only awarded to a <u>maximum of two cars</u> with your chosen engine</p>

<h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag">&nbsp;</span>Driver of the Day</h3>
<p>The FIA ‘driver of the day’ will receive an additional 10 points to their race score.</p>

<h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag">&nbsp;</span>Late User Registration</h3>
<p>Late joiners will be able to register mid-season. Late joiners will be provided additional starting points.</p>